		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Platforms that require pure Java</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">mattmatteh wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What platforms are java only ?</div>
<br />Programs running inside web browsers are generally JavaScript/Java/Flash only. One needs to be an administrator to install plug-ins written in C++, and if you're trying to install a plug-in into Internet Explorer, it additionally needs to be digitally signed with an Authenticode certificate, which many students and hobbyists cannot easily afford.
<br />
<br />Some cell phones can run midlets, or apps written in Java that use the MIDP API. They can't run C++ programs that aren't approved by the carrier. Apps for Android phones are written in the Java language, but not Java ME or Java SE.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


